    "created_at": "2015-06-24T23:02:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-24T23:03:18Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "With things as they are, `GainsStatUpgrades` doesn't work as one would expect it to. What one expects is that this trait implements four independent upgrades: e.g. if I grant a unit from TS `firepower` and `speed` upgrades, the actor should only inflict 10% more damage when attacking and move 20% more quickly. However, right now, if you just grant each of those two upgrades once, you will get full elite behavior: 30% more firepower, 66% damage taken from attacks, 50% quicker movement and 75% the reload time. This is clearly not what this trait is meant to do. Now, in order to properly fix this, a blueprint of the upgrade system's logic is necessary and needs to be agreed upon. So this is what I'm waiting for right now.\n\n`UpgradableTrait` however (and all traits that inherit from it), works correctly with things as they are.\n"
  },
