    "created_at": "2015-06-25T11:02:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-25T11:02:02Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@penev92, it was @pchote that wished to first establish what the desired functionality of the upgrade system is before actually fixing anything. If what @atlimit8 is saying should be done, i.e., if the system should be designed so that each trait uses at most one parameter (sum of all upgrade levels) instead of multiple parameters (independent upgrade levels for different upgrades), then\n- `GainsStatUpgrades` indeed needs refactoring and\n- I'd say the notifications, that the `UpgradeManager` sends, should contain only information on this one parameter (upgrade level sum) instead of also saying which upgrade triggered the latest aggregate level change.\n  That would make this PR unwanted.\n\nIf, on the other hand, traits should be allowed to provide upgrades that depend on multiple independent parameters (upgrade levels), then this PR would be OK, but the `GainsStatUpgrades` would be the only trait using this functionality and the `UpgradableTrait` should be updated (this is what I've done locally).\n\nBasically the question is - single or multiple parameters for upgrades?\n"
  },
